        {
            "id": "action",
            "instance": "0a6ef072-06a0-4c13-a76e-6077fa865011",
            "properties": [
                [
                    "name",
                    "External Remote Services"
                ],
                [
                    "ttp",
                    [
                        [
                            "tactic",
                            "TA0001"
                        ],
                        [
                            "technique",
                            "T1133"
                        ]
                    ]
                ],
                [
                    "description",
                    "External Remote Services is Bashify's highest-frequency and most consistently observed technique across 19 reports — the actor gains entry to victim environments through exposed RDP, SSH, VPN gateways, and web-based management interfaces using stolen local credentials. This node anchors all post-access operations: SSH and cloud-service lateral movement, email collection, and Telegram-based C2, with the resulting data and access used for intelligence collection or resale."
                ],
                [
                    "confidence",
                    null
                ],
